  "time_ut": 1661066684,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc0;   \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0b95\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba9",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "fire inside the hostel; Students' books were also burnt",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Peradanai police said that they have received a complaint that due to the fire that broke out in a private hostel for university students, which was run on Hintagala Road near Peradanai University, there was damage to the hostel and students' belongings including books.",
        "It has been reported that there were 20-23 students inside the said hostel yesterday night (19), and no one was hurt when the fire spread.",
        "However, the students' learning equipment, lap computers, clothes etc. were burnt in the fire.",
        "Students studying in the second year of Management Faculty of Peradana University are staying in this area and steps have been taken to provide 7500 rupees each from the Vice-Chancellor's Fund to 10 students who lost their belongings due to the fire.",
        "Peradanai Police said that the reason for the spread of the fire has not yet been revealed and that they are conducting investigations into the incident."
      ],
